text: Mayar is a mountain in the Grampians, in Angus, Scotland. It is usually climbed together with its near neighbour, Driesh. At an elevation of 928m, it is the 564th highest peak in the British Isles and the 534th tallest in Scotland. ==References== Category:Munros Category:Mountains and hills of the Eastern Highlands Category:Mountains and hills of Angus
title: Mayar (mountain)
